  "name": "Morrison CFD Hemolysis Credibility Package — CPB (Minimal Profile)",
  "description": "This package documents the credibility evidence for a CFD-based hemolysis prediction model applied to the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass operating conditions. The model has been applied in clinical research settings to identify worst-case shear-stress exposure for Class II CPB devices. A 13-factor ASME V&V 40 assessment was conducted at Model Risk Level 2; seven factors were formally assessed and six were scoped out as acceptable at MRL 2. All assessed factors meet or exceed required gradation levels, supporting an Accepted decision outcome.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cpb-worst-case-hemolysis",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/morrison-cfd-hemolysis-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-generic-pump-experimental-hemolysis",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-cfd-mesh-convergence-study"
  ],
